{"type":"message-part","messageId":"1f308e3e-c739-4853-95dd-370b6175aa6f","role":"user","index":1,"part":{"type":"text","text":"# Preserving your work\n\nSave a copy of files you create during this task to `/logs/artifacts/`. This directory is preserved after the run so outputs can be inspected. Organize with subdirectories if helpful (e.g., `/logs/artifacts/code/`, `/logs/artifacts/reports/`). The directory already exists and is writable.\n\n---\n\n# TypeScript Windmill Script — Dynamic Report String Builder\n\n## Background\n\nWindmill scripts are often used as formatting steps in a flow that assemble human-readable reports from structured data produced by earlier steps. This task involves building a multi-line report string from a set of input fields.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Create a TypeScript script at `/home/user/windmill-project/f/scripts/build_report.ts`.\n- Export an async `main` function:\n  ```typescript\n  export async function main(\n    title: string,\n    items: string[],\n    footer: string = \"End of report\"\n  )\n  ```\n- The function must return a string that is a report with:\n  - Line 1: `=== ${title} ===`\n  - Lines 2..N: each item prefixed with `- ` (a dash and space)\n  - Last line: `--- ${footer} ---`\n  - Lines joined with `\\n`\n- Create the metadata file at `/home/user/windmill-project/f/scripts/build_report.script.yaml` with:\n  - `summary: \"Build a formatted text report from a list of items\"`\n  - `language: typescript`\n\n## Implementation Guide\n\n```typescript\nexport async function main(title: string, items: string[], footer: string = \"End of report\") {\n  const lines = [\n    `=== ${title} ===`,\n    ...items.map(i => `- ${i}`),\n    `--- ${footer} ---`,\n  ];\n  return lines.join(\"\\n\");\n}\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Project path: `/home/user/windmill-project`\n- Join lines with `\\n` (newline), not `\\r\\n`\n- Item prefix is `\"- \"` (dash space)\n\n## Integrations\n\nNone."}}
